-- European shares rise early; helped by BHP
-- 
-- Fri Aug 15, 2014 03:11AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Aug 15 (Reuters) - European shares rose in early trade on Friday, gaining ground for the fourth time in five sessions, helped by BHP Billion <BLT.L> after the world's biggest miner said it could spin off assets.

At 0707 GMT, the FTSEurofirst 300 <.FTEU3> index of top European shares was up 0.3 percent at 1,333.67 points, set to post its biggest weekly gain since mid-February.